SIMPLE: shelve
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shelve
<hw>Shelve</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
furnish with shelves; <as>as, to <ex>shelve</ex> a closet or a
library</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To place on a shelf. Hence: To lay on the shelf; to
put aside; to dismiss from service; to put off indefinitely; <as>as, to
<ex>shelve</ex> an officer; to <ex>shelve</ex> a claim</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shelve</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Shelve
<hw>Shelve</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Shelved</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Shelving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Perhapss originally from the
same source as <ets>shallow</ets>, but influenced by <ets>shelf</ets> a
ledge, a platform.]</ety> <def>To incline gradually; to be slopping;
<as>as, the bottom <ex>shelves</ex> from the shore</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shelving</ent>⟦br⟧
